That was cool. Thank you. &#34;High-tech crosswalks&#34; lol as per the reporter. But the DOT guy comment was the key note... &#34;it will be interesting to see where the technology goes&#34;. He said that right after commenting &#34;we could determine for privacy issues who&#39;s driving...&#34;

Likely he said &#34;can&#39;t&#34; although the transcript shows &#34;can&#34;. Either way, you can only imagine how powerful this technology can be if sensors can read license plates and in the future, faces and instantly show on screen everything about you including the name of your dog. He also said 10, 15, 20 years ago this could not have been imagined&#34;. 

Whether this is Ouster or not, it is easy to see this system expanding, on time, from coast to coast.
